{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.3",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
    "chapterNumber": 3,
    "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3",
    "summary": "Source text for 1 Corinthians 3 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.3.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:1",
      "text": "And I, brethren, could not speak unto you as unto spiritual, but as unto carnal, even as unto babes in Christ.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.3.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:2",
      "text": "I have fed you with milk, and not with meat: for hitherto ye were not able to bear it, neither yet now are ye able.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.3.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:3",
      "text": "For ye are yet carnal: for whereas there is among you envying, and strife, and divisions, are ye not carnal, and walk as men?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.3.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:4",
      "text": "For while one saith, I am of Paul; and another, I am of Apollos; are ye not carnal?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.3.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:5",
      "text": "Who then is Paul, and who is Apollos, but ministers by whom ye believed, even as the Lord gave to every man?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.3.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:6",
      "text": "I have planted, Apollos watered; but God gave the increase.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.3.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:7",
      "text": "So then neither is he that planteth any thing, neither he that watereth; but God that giveth the increase.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.3.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:8",
      "text": "Now he that planteth and he that watereth are one: and every man shall receive his own reward according to his own labour.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.3.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:9",
      "text": "For we are labourers together with God: ye are God’s husbandry, ye are God’s building.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.3.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:10",
      "text": "According to the grace of God which is given unto me, as a wise masterbuilder, I have laid the foundation, and another buildeth thereon. But let every man take heed how he buildeth thereupon.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.3.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:11",
      "text": "For other foundation can no man lay than that is laid, which is Jesus Christ.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.3.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:12",
      "text": "Now if any man build upon this foundation gold, silver, precious stones, wood, hay, stubble;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.3.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:13",
      "text": "Every man’s work shall be made manifest: for the day shall declare it, because it shall be revealed by fire; and the fire shall try every man’s work of what sort it is.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.3.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:14",
      "text": "If any man’s work abide which he hath built thereupon, he shall receive a reward.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.3.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:15",
      "text": "If any man’s work shall be burned, he shall suffer loss: but he himself shall be saved; yet so as by fire.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.3.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:16",
      "text": "Know ye not that ye are the temple of God, and that the Spirit of God dwelleth in you?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.3.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:17",
      "text": "If any man defile the temple of God, him shall God destroy; for the temple of God is holy, which temple ye are.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.3.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:18",
      "text": "Let no man deceive himself. If any man among you seemeth to be wise in this world, let him become a fool, that he may be wise.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.3.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:19",
      "text": "For the wisdom of this world is foolishness with God. For it is written, He taketh the wise in their own craftiness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.3.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:20",
      "text": "And again, The Lord knoweth the thoughts of the wise, that they are vain.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.3.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:21",
      "text": "Therefore let no man glory in men. For all things are yours;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.3.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:22",
      "text": "Whether Paul, or Apollos, or Cephas, or the world, or life, or death, or things present, or things to come; all are yours;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:first-corinthians.3.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 3:23",
      "text": "And ye are Christ’s; and Christ is God’s.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
